  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting IDPs through an integrated shelter and NFI response in Borno State</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed 7 months project is complementary to ACTED&apos;s currently ongoing shelter and NFI distribution project funded through the first allocation of the NHF and is intended to complement ACTED&apos;s CCCM project proposed also under the 2nd NHF allocation. The proposed project has two main objectives: 1) To contribute to improved living conditions in Mafa GSS camp supporting the relocation of people from Camp B in Mafa through the construction of 1,000 Dikwa shelters in Camp A (Girls Secondary Camp) and 2) To provide life-saving shelter and non-food items assistance through prepositioning and distribution of critical assistance in the reception center in Custom House area as part of the new arrival strategy. As such, the proposed project is intertwined with the second project ACTED is proposing under the second NHF allocation round. 

The proposed project is in line with the NHF allocation strategy by supporting priority four in the NHF allocation paper which supports the Provision of emergency shelters kits and NFI kits to improve shelter conditions and is supporting the objective to &#x201C;Support life-saving activities and alleviate suffering through integrated and coordinated humanitarian response focusing on the most vulnerable people&#x201D; of the HRP.</narrative>
  </description>
